@node "ART_DO5o" "Directory Opus V5.O"
                    DIRECTORY OPUS VERSION 5.0


The new version of Directory Opus has been completely rewritten and is 
now much more powerful than the earlier versions. It still retains all the 
functions of the old program: being able to copy rename and delete files, 
play animations ect. ect. But it's look  and method of operation have 
changed dramatically. 

Perhaps the most significant change in terms of use is that the popular 
two sided display, with rows of buttons at the bottom has been replaced 
by a dedicated screen with multiple windows, with buttons along the top 
of the windows.

To copy files you now open a window to the source directory, i.e. the 
drawer from where you wish to copy from, then open a window for the 
destination and click on one of the small buttons along the top of the 
source window.

At first this seems like a massive step backwards, but if you play around 
with it for a while you will realize that this approach gives the program 
massive power. Multiple source and destination windows can be 
opened, so you could copy a drawer from df0: to Ram:, the HD and df1: 
at the same time. 

In essence, version 5 continues the trend of the earlier versions of being 
configurable, which was why it became so popular, but takes it to new  
levels. Not only can you configure the name of every button, and it's op-
eration, you can also edit the menus and define whether icons or text 
buttons are used. It's this level of configurability that gives the 
program it's power - you can literally make it look like anything you 
want!. It can even become the default Workbench screen - so you don't have
a Workbench at all - DirOpus becomes the new frontend of our Amiga. 

Another major change in the program is that it now multitasks internally. 
This means that you will be able to copy, delete, un-LhA and format 
disks all at the same time (quite a handy thing for us traders (well all of
us I guess! ), to be able to unDMS a disk while you're LhA'ing some files 
and copying some other files from your download dir. All in the same 
program. No need for 5 shells running in the background.) 

All in all this new version looks really impressive. The only problem 
might be, that it takes some time to get used to the new user-interface, 
because it isn't as easy to use as the old one, but if you configure it 
right, you'll soon see the advantages of using DirOpus as a new frontend
for your Amiga.

And as a final solution, you can always configure it to look like the old 
(version 4.xx) Opus.

All I can say is: Keep your eyes open, cos DirOpus 5.0 is gonna hit a 
board near you, real soon! (So start saving your credz! :)  )

           PLEXER
@endnode



